# Level_Design

## 1. Applies when
Linear levels, boxed levels, dungeons, chapter-based maps, or arena maps.

## 2. This document owns
Level objectives; spatial structure; routes; pacing; encounter placement; resource
points; checkpoints; guidance; fail recovery.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Large-map structure (that is World_Design); enemy raw stats; full cutscene scripts.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Objectives · 3. Layout · 4. Routes · 5. Encounter placement ·
6. Pacing · 7. Resources & checkpoints · 8. Guidance · 9. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Level vs World — a single playable space vs large-map structure.
- Level vs Encounter — placement/count vs composition/rules.
- Level vs Script — triggers vs cutscene performance.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Level does not re-define encounter rules; it references Encounter_Design.
- Guidance/routes must not be mixed into World_Design (map structure).
